NAN Okada Media, organisers of the annual Nollywood Week Film Festival, have selected top Nigerian movies for screening at the event scheduled for May 3 to May 9, in Paris, France. The selected movies include ‘Isoken’, a romantic comedy directed by Jade Osiberu and ‘Kasala’, directed by Emamodeviefe Edosio, as well as ‘Silvia’ and ‘The lost Cafe and Alter Ego’. Movies scheduled for special screening at the event are’Banana Island Ghost’,’Potato Potahto’ and ‘The Wedding Party 2’. Now in its sixth edition, Nollywood Week Paris is a yearly film festival that showcases the best of Nigerian film industry, aimed at attracting global audience and more sustainable distribution mechanism. The grand finale of the festival is where the prestigious Prix du Public (Audience Award) is presented to the best filmmaker, among other prizes to participants.